reviewText: How films like these gain such a devoted following is, quite simply, unfathomable to me. Why talented, heralded actors like Dustin Hoffman and Robert DeNiro choose to make films like this is even more unfathomable - Ishtar was Citizen Kane compared to either of these excreble excuses for entertainment. I saw both of these on the recommendation of people I'm close to; it's clear that, though I love them both dearly, their taste in movies and mine are very, very different. I haven't laughed so little since I saw Camille Claudel - but that won't mean much to most of you. Oh, well.
summary: Painful, unfunny, vulgar, predictable...and those are the good comments
Title: The Circle of Trust Collection: (Meet the Parents / Meet the Fockers)

reviewText: Ben Stiller, along with a great cast, make this two-part movie set a must see for everyone.  Adult humor is involved and may not be suitable for children.  The laughs keep coming though.  Ben Stiller is trying to get into his new father-in-laws "circle of trust", but is really bad at it until Ben learns a secret about his future father-in-law.  Later, Ben has his own circle of trust, and his now father-in-law must earn his way in.
Title: The Circle of Trust Collection: (Meet the Parents / Meet the Fockers)
